WEBVTT

00:01.168 --> 00:02.085
Previously on
Cruel Summer...

00:02.085 --> 00:03.837
The sheriff's
been digging around.

00:03.837 --> 00:04.755
I had to strike back.

00:04.755 --> 00:06.423
Someone planted it there.

00:06.423 --> 00:09.676
You know Iz.
She's capable of
absolutely anything.

00:09.676 --> 00:11.386
Maybe you aren't that into Luke.

00:11.386 --> 00:12.971
That would be
a good thing because?

00:12.971 --> 00:15.057
Because I think I am.

00:15.057 --> 00:17.976
Everyone already believes that
they saw me on that tape, right?

00:17.976 --> 00:20.812
-Yeah.
-So let's make sure
that it stays that way.

00:20.812 --> 00:23.732
The more that they find out
about you on the night
Luke disappeared,

00:23.732 --> 00:25.526
the more that
they find out about me.

00:25.526 --> 00:26.818
You need to tell
Isabella to leave.

00:26.818 --> 00:29.029
I can't stand to be
around her anymore.

00:29.029 --> 00:31.657
But I think it's best
if you stay somewhere else
while this all plays out.

00:31.657 --> 00:33.867
There's something under my bed
that Megan wanted me
to get rid of.

00:33.867 --> 00:36.995
"When I heard that Luke drowned,
I knew I had to contact you."

00:36.995 --> 00:40.874
"When I was in Chatham
last summer, I realized you
didn't know the full picture."

00:40.874 --> 00:42.334
Oh, my God.

00:42.334 --> 00:44.044
(modem beeping and buzzing)

00:55.055 --> 00:57.391
(New Radicals playing
"You Get What You Give")

01:01.979 --> 01:03.063
♪ Oh... ♪

01:06.400 --> 01:07.609
You look great.

01:07.609 --> 01:09.152
I love your hair like that.

01:09.152 --> 01:10.612
Thanks.

01:10.612 --> 01:12.948
Thought I'd try something new
for the party today.

01:12.948 --> 01:16.118
So, about that.

01:16.118 --> 01:19.121
-I broke up with Luke.
-You what?

01:19.121 --> 01:22.583
-It's his birthday.
-Which is why I did it
last night.

01:22.583 --> 01:25.043
I couldn't keep seeing him
now that I know how you feel.

01:25.043 --> 01:26.920
-I didn't ask you to do that.
-I know.

01:26.920 --> 01:30.048
I wanted to. He clearly
has feelings for you.

01:30.048 --> 01:31.925
And you guys are like
the end game, so...

01:31.925 --> 01:33.594
Why wait?

01:33.594 --> 01:36.096
Are you sure about this?
I thought you liked him.

01:36.096 --> 01:39.683
It was never going to be
anything more than a summer
fling between the two of us.

01:42.936 --> 01:45.105
What did he say?
Like, how did he take it?

01:45.105 --> 01:48.191
He was surprised, for sure,
but, um...

01:48.191 --> 01:50.944
he took it pretty well.

01:50.944 --> 01:53.280
Okay.

01:53.280 --> 01:56.742
The party's gonna be a blast.
He'll forget all about me.

01:58.368 --> 01:59.870
Plus, one look at you,

01:59.870 --> 02:01.705
and he'll realize
that what he wants

02:01.705 --> 02:04.041
has been in front of him
this whole time.

02:13.216 --> 02:14.384
Isabella:
Hey.

02:14.384 --> 02:16.470
Almost ready.

02:16.470 --> 02:18.347
I'm so glad we're doing this.

02:18.347 --> 02:19.723
The Chatham Plunge
is the bomb.

02:19.723 --> 02:21.099
Luke and I have never
missed one.

02:21.099 --> 02:23.310
-You're gonna love it.
-(computer chimes)

02:23.310 --> 02:24.728
Wait, how cold is it again?

02:28.190 --> 02:31.068
Um, shoot, I, um...

02:31.068 --> 02:32.444
I'm gonna
have to bail, actually.

02:32.444 --> 02:34.112
-Why?
-I'm sorry, really.

02:34.112 --> 02:36.490
It's, um...
it's this paperwork

02:36.490 --> 02:38.617
that I have to send to U Dub
before the end of the year.

02:38.617 --> 02:40.118
-You can't do it later?
-No.

02:40.118 --> 02:41.995
Deadline's today.

02:41.995 --> 02:43.997
It's for the scholarship,
so it's a big deal.

02:43.997 --> 02:45.916
(computer chimes)

02:49.920 --> 02:51.672
Um, we'll hang tonight.
I promise.

02:51.672 --> 02:53.465
(upbeat music playing)

02:56.134 --> 02:57.928
♪ Confess my faults ♪

02:57.928 --> 03:01.014
♪ To keep
your conscience clear ♪

03:02.391 --> 03:04.393
(music continues on headset)

03:12.526 --> 03:13.902
(computer chimes)

03:19.825 --> 03:20.951
Debbie:
Did you sleep at all?

03:23.995 --> 03:25.038
Not really.

03:27.749 --> 03:29.209
Luke would have been 18 today.

03:30.961 --> 03:33.547
A year ago, I was planning
his 17th birthday party.

03:36.133 --> 03:38.093
Now there's a memorial instead.

03:39.594 --> 03:40.929
It's so hard
to believe he's gone.

03:46.059 --> 03:47.519
Where did you get the laptop?

03:49.813 --> 03:51.022
A friend.

03:51.022 --> 03:52.399
Who?

03:54.109 --> 03:55.986
(music continues loudly)

04:00.240 --> 04:02.075
(electronic squelching)

04:22.554 --> 04:25.140
Brent:
Couldn't sleep?

04:25.140 --> 04:26.141
No.

04:28.101 --> 04:30.103
Yeah. Me either.

04:33.356 --> 04:34.608
(sighs)

04:38.737 --> 04:40.697
You know, he...

04:40.697 --> 04:43.116
he would've loved being
the center of attention.

04:43.116 --> 04:44.701
(laughing)

04:47.496 --> 04:48.663
"All Eyez On Me."

04:52.334 --> 04:54.920
God, he was the worst rapper.

04:54.920 --> 04:57.923
Just... what was it,
DJ Just Stop?

04:57.923 --> 05:00.675
Remember when he used
to try to beatbox?

05:02.052 --> 05:04.095
Yeah.

05:04.095 --> 05:06.139
Yeah, it was just...

05:06.139 --> 05:07.682
spitting everywhere.

05:16.066 --> 05:17.734
I was such a dick to him.

05:19.361 --> 05:20.654
Yeah, you were.

05:23.114 --> 05:25.325
But you're kind of a dick
to everyone, so...

05:28.578 --> 05:29.538
Yeah.

05:32.707 --> 05:34.167
Still, you know,

05:34.167 --> 05:36.253
he didn't deserve it.

05:45.679 --> 05:47.514
(upbeat music playing)

05:57.023 --> 05:59.359
Finally. How long
does it take to get some ice?

05:59.359 --> 06:01.361
(straining)

06:01.361 --> 06:03.530
Had to make a few stops.

06:03.530 --> 06:06.241
Lily's staying at a friend's
and my mom's not getting home
until like 10:00,

06:06.241 --> 06:08.368
so we'll have the whole house
to ourselves for the party.

06:08.368 --> 06:09.870
Something's different.

06:11.496 --> 06:14.332
I showered.
Did you bring the saw horses?

06:14.332 --> 06:16.835
-Yeah, I already set it up.
-Okay. Can you run this
through the living room?

06:16.835 --> 06:18.753
'Cause the socket outside
might blow a fuse.

06:18.753 --> 06:22.299
Just relax, Sarge.
All right? We got this.

06:22.299 --> 06:25.510
Okay. I just want this to be
the best birthday ever.

06:25.510 --> 06:27.262
Get Luke's mind off
of everything.

06:27.262 --> 06:30.015
What, you mean being dumped
like a chump?

06:30.015 --> 06:31.057
Just keep the import

06:31.057 --> 06:32.142
in her trailer

06:32.142 --> 06:33.268
and it'll be fine.

06:33.268 --> 06:35.103
-Dude.
-You know, I always say

06:35.103 --> 06:37.105
that the best way
to get over someone

06:37.105 --> 06:39.190
is to get under someone else.

06:39.190 --> 06:41.776
Right. Well, you say a lot
of crap and no one's buying it.

06:44.738 --> 06:47.407
Just trust me. All right?

06:47.407 --> 06:50.869
This party's gonna be something
that Luke will never forget.

07:05.842 --> 07:08.887
Come on, come on, come on.
One more, one more.

07:08.887 --> 07:11.014
Go, go, go.
There you go, good!

07:11.014 --> 07:13.892
(chuckles) Good!

07:13.892 --> 07:17.228
Now, that's how you build
the power. (chuckles)

07:17.228 --> 07:19.439
I could... I could be
in here all year,

07:19.439 --> 07:21.024
I still wouldn't look
like you.

07:21.024 --> 07:24.194
You see? That attitude right
there is part of your problem.

07:24.194 --> 07:26.613
If you don't lead
with confidence,

07:26.613 --> 07:28.823
bullies can smell that
from a mile away.

07:28.823 --> 07:30.950
It's primal.

07:30.950 --> 07:33.912
Yeah, well,
Brent's more of a primate.

07:33.912 --> 07:35.914
Yeah, well...

07:35.914 --> 07:39.834
family knows how to push buttons
better than anyone.

07:39.834 --> 07:44.339
My dad used to be
a "my way or the highway"
kind of guy.

07:44.339 --> 07:47.008
Used to bully the hell out of me
and my sister when we were kids.

07:47.008 --> 07:49.469
You? I can't see that.

07:49.469 --> 07:52.514
Yep. He didn't want me
to go into law enforcement,

07:52.514 --> 07:54.683
thought it was beneath me.

07:54.683 --> 07:56.059
You didn't listen, though.

07:56.059 --> 07:58.978
Nope.

07:58.978 --> 08:00.939
Biggest lesson I've learned...

08:03.692 --> 08:05.485
was to be my own person.

08:05.485 --> 08:09.030
You know, don't let
people tell you what's what.

08:09.030 --> 08:11.449
Unless it's a beautiful woman.

08:11.449 --> 08:13.785
Then we'll just let 'em think
they call the shots.

08:13.785 --> 08:16.621
But always make sure
you have the final say.

08:16.621 --> 08:17.789
Totally.

08:17.789 --> 08:19.207
All right.

08:19.207 --> 08:20.291
Come on, one more.

08:22.961 --> 08:25.046
(guests laughing)

08:25.046 --> 08:26.631
Tim:
Oh, these'll get you lit!

08:26.631 --> 08:30.009
Whoo! Let's get
this party started!

08:30.009 --> 08:32.095
Yeah, let's go!

08:32.095 --> 08:34.305
You've killed it, as usual.

08:34.305 --> 08:35.598
Oh, thanks.

08:35.598 --> 08:38.518
I'm not used
to you with the ponytail.

08:38.518 --> 08:41.020
But you always look fly, though.

08:41.020 --> 08:43.273
(guests laughing, joking)

08:43.273 --> 08:45.233
Ah, let me grab
some paper towels.

08:45.233 --> 08:46.568
Eric:
Luke's here!

08:46.568 --> 08:48.695
-(cheering)
-Happy birthday!

08:48.695 --> 08:50.363
Thank you, thank you.

08:50.363 --> 08:52.907
-Happy birthday!
-Oh, wow!

08:52.907 --> 08:54.576
This is rad, Megan, thank you.

08:54.576 --> 08:55.744
What are best friends for?

08:55.744 --> 08:58.246
Getting each other naked wasted?

08:58.246 --> 08:59.539
Uh, is Parker here?

08:59.539 --> 09:00.582
Yeah, she's out back.

09:02.917 --> 09:04.627
He's actually
being really cool today.

09:04.627 --> 09:06.796
He's trying
to make me feel better
in his own screwed-up way,

09:06.796 --> 09:08.214
you know?

09:08.214 --> 09:11.468
Uh, is, uh...
is Isabella here?

09:11.468 --> 09:13.511
Brent thought it'd be weird
for her to be here,

09:13.511 --> 09:15.722
so she's just laying low.

09:15.722 --> 09:17.682
Tell her to come.
I'm cool.

09:17.682 --> 09:18.850
Really?

09:20.894 --> 09:23.188
Yeah, I mean... mostly.

09:23.188 --> 09:25.190
I'll pace myself.

09:25.190 --> 09:26.066
I'll help.

09:29.778 --> 09:30.904
See? Slowing you right down.

09:32.363 --> 09:33.698
What did you do
with your hair?

09:33.698 --> 09:36.367
I haven't seen it
down like this in forever.

09:36.367 --> 09:38.244
Just felt like changing it up.

09:38.244 --> 09:42.457
(laughing, joking)

09:42.457 --> 09:44.042
(in sing-song) Luke!

09:44.042 --> 09:46.586
We have five shots
with your name on them!

09:49.798 --> 09:51.007
-(clapping)
-That's all!

09:51.007 --> 09:53.176
(laughter)

09:53.176 --> 09:54.094
Eric:
Ooh!

10:06.731 --> 10:08.775
Are those the police files
on Lisa's death?

10:08.775 --> 10:10.944
-From St. Barts?
-Yeah.

10:10.944 --> 10:12.987
I thought Tom said
those were sealed?

10:12.987 --> 10:14.239
They were.
But I found a way.

10:18.076 --> 10:20.245
Someone who was at the party
said that Isabella

10:20.245 --> 10:22.163
convinced Lisa
to go swimming that night,

10:22.163 --> 10:24.082
even though
she was clearly drunk.

10:24.082 --> 10:25.917
People heard them fighting
in the water

10:25.917 --> 10:27.669
right around the time
that Lisa drowned.

10:27.669 --> 10:30.588
She left St. Barts
that night by helicopter

10:30.588 --> 10:32.757
before anyone
could ask questions.

10:32.757 --> 10:35.135
So she's a fugitive?

10:35.135 --> 10:38.179
The case was closed
due to insufficient evidence.

10:38.179 --> 10:40.890
Seems pretty sufficient to me.

10:40.890 --> 10:42.892
Her parents must've used
their connections

10:42.892 --> 10:44.310
to keep it quiet.

10:46.354 --> 10:47.856
A falling out
with her best friend,

10:47.856 --> 10:49.858
and then someone drowns.

10:49.858 --> 10:51.609
I mean, it's... it's...

10:51.609 --> 10:53.278
Terrible.

10:53.278 --> 10:55.113
Familiar.

11:00.160 --> 11:02.120
Whidbey Island
has the best trails.

11:02.120 --> 11:04.789
I've been going camping there
with my parents
since I was a baby.

11:04.789 --> 11:08.293
(laughing) I'm just
picturing you in your diaper,
just filming everyone.

11:08.293 --> 11:10.920
What you mean, in my diaper?

11:10.920 --> 11:12.422
No, stop.

11:12.422 --> 11:14.841
Luke: What is this?
What are we doing?

11:14.841 --> 11:17.635
-It's called a Hurricane.
-Okay.

11:17.635 --> 11:19.512
-Does it rip your top off?
-You'll see.

11:19.512 --> 11:20.597
Okay, hit that.

11:20.597 --> 11:21.639
Okay.

11:24.100 --> 11:26.102
(laughter)

11:26.102 --> 11:27.437
Do me next!

11:27.437 --> 11:29.147
Did you see that?

11:29.147 --> 11:30.815
Yeah.

11:30.815 --> 11:33.109
So, um...

11:33.109 --> 11:37.572
My parents said I could bring
a friend when we go back
to Whidbey in August.

11:37.572 --> 11:39.532
Uh... would you want to come?

11:52.212 --> 11:54.214
-Megan?
-Hmm?

11:55.798 --> 11:56.925
I get it.

11:56.925 --> 11:58.676
A great party
doesn't host itself.

11:58.676 --> 12:00.720
Uh... Find me later.

12:00.720 --> 12:02.013
Yeah. Totally.

12:07.477 --> 12:08.895
That boy has it bad for you.

12:08.895 --> 12:10.438
I know.

12:10.438 --> 12:12.523
And he's so nice.

12:12.523 --> 12:14.150
I think I have
to break up with him.

12:14.150 --> 12:16.110
(high-pitched voice)
Do I sound silly?

12:16.110 --> 12:18.696
-(laughter)
-Luke: Hey, are you not
going to do the Hurricane?

12:18.696 --> 12:20.406
Are you sure you're not having
second thoughts?

12:20.406 --> 12:22.450
Yeah, I'm positive.

12:22.450 --> 12:23.618
He's all yours.

12:35.630 --> 12:37.924
I told you a couple days ago,
something's up with her.

12:37.924 --> 12:39.717
Yeah. You were right.

12:39.717 --> 12:41.427
I mean, she's never
missed a Plunge.

12:41.427 --> 12:45.098
She was totally coming
until she got that message.

12:45.098 --> 12:47.308
It was probably from Ned.

12:47.308 --> 12:50.395
I swear, it's like
she'll take any excuse
to blow me off lately.

12:50.395 --> 12:52.855
Guess you're taking your trash
out in public now, Chambers.

12:54.274 --> 12:56.317
Hey, Isabella,
can I plunge into you?

12:56.317 --> 12:57.652
You're pathetic.

12:57.652 --> 12:59.070
Wait, you like
an audience, right?

12:59.070 --> 13:00.655
We can just do it right here.

13:00.655 --> 13:03.241
It's not like you've ever
done it with anyone ever.

13:03.241 --> 13:07.453
So why don't you two
go play with yourselves
and leave her alone?

13:07.453 --> 13:09.122
Whatever, dude.

13:09.122 --> 13:10.707
Eric:
You've changed.

13:13.293 --> 13:15.545
Hey, they're assholes, okay?
Don't worry about them.

13:15.545 --> 13:17.714
Eventually they'll
move on to something else.

13:17.714 --> 13:20.258
(sighs) You give them
too much credit.

13:20.258 --> 13:21.843
But thanks.

13:25.513 --> 13:29.225
All right,
are we doing this or what?

13:29.225 --> 13:31.728
-Race you in.
-(upbeat music playing)

13:31.728 --> 13:33.646
♪ I can't believe you did it ♪

13:33.646 --> 13:35.356
♪ Oh-ho-ho ♪

13:35.356 --> 13:37.317
♪ In the end we both ♪

13:37.317 --> 13:39.986
♪ Played our part
in a TV show ♪

13:39.986 --> 13:42.822
(music slows, fades out)

13:49.245 --> 13:52.915
Debbie. There's something
under my bed that Megan
wanted me to get rid of.

13:52.915 --> 13:54.500
You should ask her why.

14:14.353 --> 14:18.441
♪ Another misty morning ♪

14:18.441 --> 14:21.736
♪ Another stormy night... ♪

14:24.197 --> 14:25.656
Um...

14:27.575 --> 14:29.160
Happy birthday.

14:29.160 --> 14:31.454
Luke:
Thanks.

14:31.454 --> 14:33.956
Megan totally
crushed this party, huh?

14:33.956 --> 14:36.667
-Just like everything else.
-Yeah, so...

14:36.667 --> 14:40.797
traditionally, in our culture,
when you dump someone,

14:40.797 --> 14:42.799
you don't crash their party.

14:44.634 --> 14:46.135
It's whatever.

14:46.135 --> 14:47.553
Ignore him.

14:47.553 --> 14:49.347
It's all good.

14:49.347 --> 14:51.432
I didn't wanna be tied down
senior year anyway.

14:53.434 --> 14:55.228
"Traditionally,
in your culture"?

14:55.228 --> 14:57.313
Where is that, Douchebag Island?

15:01.651 --> 15:04.445
Jack!

15:04.445 --> 15:06.280
We need to talk.

15:06.280 --> 15:07.573
I've gotta go.

15:10.535 --> 15:12.703
It's been almost two weeks,
still no arrests.

15:12.703 --> 15:14.747
What the hell kind of
investigation are you running?

15:14.747 --> 15:17.291
I know today must be incredibly
difficult for you, right?

15:17.291 --> 15:18.751
Sit down,
let's talk about this--

15:18.751 --> 15:21.003
Why are you not charging anyone?

15:21.003 --> 15:23.422
I can't go jumping
at every half-baked theory.

15:23.422 --> 15:25.133
So instead you sit on your ass
and you do nothing?

15:37.228 --> 15:38.771
(door clatters shut)

15:40.481 --> 15:43.359
I'm following the evidence,
seeing where it leads.

15:43.359 --> 15:46.445
It leads straight to Isabella,
if you ask me.

15:46.445 --> 15:49.657
I mean, her fingerprints
were on the gun,

15:49.657 --> 15:52.827
her bag of money
was at the cabin.

15:52.827 --> 15:56.664
Trust me, I am working
around the clock,
leaving no stone unturned.

15:56.664 --> 16:00.126
Um... I'm done waiting, Jack.

16:00.126 --> 16:02.879
I'm hiring an investigator,
someone who can
get the job done,

16:02.879 --> 16:05.882
someone who can get Luke
some real justice.

16:14.640 --> 16:16.475
Jeff:
Wanna team up?

16:16.475 --> 16:17.852
Yeah, sure. Okay.

16:19.687 --> 16:21.439
Okay!

16:21.439 --> 16:23.316
Welcome to the first annual

16:23.316 --> 16:25.651
Luke Chambers Invitational
Beer Pong tournament.

16:25.651 --> 16:27.069
Winner gets a beej!

16:27.069 --> 16:29.113
What if it's a girl, you tool?

16:29.113 --> 16:30.907
-Then you get to give one!
-Yeah.

16:30.907 --> 16:34.285
Uh, it is teams of two, so...

16:36.078 --> 16:38.831
I call Megan as my teammate.

16:38.831 --> 16:40.833
'Cause you have very good
eye-hand combination.

16:40.833 --> 16:42.126
Coordination.

16:42.126 --> 16:44.212
Think you need a break
from the brewskis.

16:44.212 --> 16:46.088
We're gonna drink
right now, anyway.

16:46.088 --> 16:47.590
Sorry, it's his birthday.

16:47.590 --> 16:49.300
It's cool.

16:49.300 --> 16:50.635
We're gonna crush this.

16:50.635 --> 16:52.178
Hell yeah, we are.

16:52.178 --> 16:54.931
Um... wanna play together?

16:54.931 --> 16:56.766
Sure.

16:56.766 --> 16:58.226
(laughing)

17:14.617 --> 17:16.744
I was thinking about you.

17:16.744 --> 17:18.412
Today must be really hard.

17:20.873 --> 17:22.667
Yeah, thanks, um...

17:22.667 --> 17:25.044
I'm actually here
to talk to Megan.

17:25.044 --> 17:27.463
Jack said we should limit
our interactions.

17:27.463 --> 17:29.215
Okay, screw Jack.
He's not delivering justice,

17:29.215 --> 17:30.841
he's not gonna make any demands.

17:32.885 --> 17:34.428
I just need to talk to her.

17:34.428 --> 17:36.847
I'm hearing
all the crazy rumors.

17:36.847 --> 17:38.808
I'm gonna need some answers.

17:38.808 --> 17:39.725
She's not here.

17:42.061 --> 17:43.354
Her car's right there, Debbie.

17:49.193 --> 17:51.279
This stuff in the news...
Megan was pregnant?

17:51.279 --> 17:53.155
Isabella's money at the cabin?

17:53.155 --> 17:55.825
If the girls
are hiding something,
I need to know what it is.

17:55.825 --> 17:58.369
And I need to hear it
out of Megan's mouth.

17:58.369 --> 17:59.579
Please.

17:59.579 --> 18:01.831
I wish I could help.

18:01.831 --> 18:04.208
Debbie.

18:04.208 --> 18:06.210
She's not home.

18:06.210 --> 18:07.461
Okay.

18:12.425 --> 18:14.010
You can't hide her forever.

18:23.978 --> 18:27.356
Oh! You look like a drowned rat.

18:27.356 --> 18:29.567
I grabbed the wrong towel.

18:29.567 --> 18:31.485
Yeah, I almost feel bad for you.

18:34.697 --> 18:35.865
C'mere.

18:35.865 --> 18:37.199
(laughing) Really?

18:37.199 --> 18:39.243
-Yeah, you can share.
-Thank you, thank you.

18:43.331 --> 18:44.624
(Isabella sighs)

18:44.624 --> 18:46.626
This is a dumb
American tradition.

18:46.626 --> 18:48.127
Yeah, I know.

18:48.127 --> 18:50.254
That's why we only do it
once a year.

18:50.254 --> 18:53.758
It takes us a full 12 months
to forget how cold the water is.

18:53.758 --> 18:55.009
Oh, my God.

18:57.803 --> 18:59.347
He wears that thing all year.

19:02.683 --> 19:06.354
Ned: I'm glad you could come.
I could really use your help.

19:06.354 --> 19:09.732
Megan:
Wow, Ned, your house is huge.

19:09.732 --> 19:12.568
Thanks. I don't get
a lot of visitors here.

19:14.070 --> 19:15.988
-(buzzer sounds)
-(door rattles)

19:21.994 --> 19:23.245
Whoa. Uh...

19:32.588 --> 19:34.423
Cool, you have fiber in here.

19:34.423 --> 19:35.841
Yeah.

19:35.841 --> 19:37.635
I've been reading about that.

19:39.261 --> 19:41.180
Oh, uh...

19:41.180 --> 19:43.349
Let's... get to work here.

19:43.349 --> 19:47.645
So, uh, my security software.

19:47.645 --> 19:49.563
Designed it myself.

19:49.563 --> 19:52.525
I have window and door sensors
throughout the house

19:52.525 --> 19:54.402
and they check in
with the server

19:54.402 --> 19:56.320
every minute, on the minute.

19:56.320 --> 19:59.865
So, if anything happens
that's not supposed to,

19:59.865 --> 20:03.202
like a door or a window opens
even just a crack,

20:03.202 --> 20:07.331
the sensors don't call home
and the system locks down.

20:07.331 --> 20:08.874
Okay.

20:08.874 --> 20:11.335
So on New Year's,

20:11.335 --> 20:14.171
when the calendar
jumps ahead to 2000

20:14.171 --> 20:16.298
and the system clock
turns over...

20:16.298 --> 20:18.092
you're afraid that the sensors
won't call home?

20:18.092 --> 20:19.635
Right.

20:19.635 --> 20:21.804
And the system won't
register the new time,

20:21.804 --> 20:23.472
and it'll lock down the house?

20:23.472 --> 20:26.142
Precisely. That's why I need
to kick the tires on this

20:26.142 --> 20:27.643
ahead of Y2K.

20:27.643 --> 20:32.356
So, why don't you go ahead
and roll the clocks forward,

20:32.356 --> 20:34.483
and we'll see
if it goes haywire?

20:34.483 --> 20:36.569
Okay.

20:36.569 --> 20:39.196
I really appreciate you asking
me to do this, by the way.

20:39.196 --> 20:42.074
Um... you've been so helpful
the last couple of months,

20:42.074 --> 20:44.577
answering all my questions
and giving advice.

20:44.577 --> 20:47.079
I feel like I can trust you.

20:47.079 --> 20:49.165
You can. I got this.

21:01.635 --> 21:03.721
(buzzer sounds, lock clicks)

21:11.854 --> 21:13.981
(cheering)

21:13.981 --> 21:15.816
All right, let's go, baby bro.

21:15.816 --> 21:17.318
Smash that ho.

21:17.318 --> 21:18.611
All right, let's take it easy.

21:18.611 --> 21:20.029
Shut your face, Brent.

21:23.157 --> 21:25.242
Nobody beats Team Chambers, bro.

21:25.242 --> 21:27.745
Megan's took all your shots.
You've hit, like, two?

21:27.745 --> 21:29.580
